hits.description:
This is a grass and natural surface trail. Along the route, there is a tunnel with a little stream that runs under a road. It is shallow water and there are stones to balance on or you can walk on the edge of the tunnel. There is some terrain up and down big hills. 

Accessibility: Visitors using wheelchairs, mobility equipment, or strollers may need all-terrain tires or adaptive/motorized equipment for the surface type and grade. Visitors using wheelchairs, mobility equipment, or strollers may need assistance along this entire route due to the consistent sections above a 5% grade (especially if using manual equipment).

Accessible Parking:
Number of designated accessible spaces: 2 at the trailhead;
Number of van-accessible spaces with access aisles: 2;
Parking lot surface: paved.

Trail Details:
Trail surface: a natural surface (dirt, grass);
Average trail width: 8 feet;
Estimated average grade category: moderately steep (5-8%) and steep (8-12%) with steeper sections at about 0.5-0.6, 1.1-1.3, 1.6-1.7, and 2.1 miles when going north;
Estimated cross slope: double track along some of the trail creating an uneven cross-slope;
Known barriers: tunnel with water running through it at about 1.4 miles when going north.

This is a paved and gravel trail with good scenery. It is wide enough for sharing comfortably with other bikers and trail users. There is some elevation change with easy-to-moderate hills.

Accessibility: Visitors using wheelchairs, mobility equipment, or strollers may need all-terrain tires or adaptive/motorized equipment for the surface type and grade. 

Accessible Parking:
Number of designated accessible spaces: 4 at the trailhead;
Number of van-accessible spaces with access aisles: 4;
Parking lot surface: paved.

Trail Details:
Trail surface: paved asphalt, gravel;
Average trail width: 6 feet;
Estimated average grade category: mostly gentle (5% or less).
